27rtc::Thread* MaybeStartThread(rtc::Thread* old_thread,
28 const std::string& thread_name,
29 bool with_socket_server,
30 std::unique_ptr<rtc::Thread>& thread_holder) {
31 if (old_thread) {
32 return old_thread;
33 }
34 if (with_socket_server) {
35 thread_holder = rtc::Thread::CreateWithSocketServer();
36 } else {
37 thread_holder = rtc::Thread::Create();
38 }
39 thread_holder->SetName(thread_name, nullptr);
40 thread_holder->Start();
41 return thread_holder.get();
42}
43
44rtc::Thread* MaybeWrapThread(rtc::Thread* signaling_thread,
45 bool& wraps_current_thread) {
46 wraps_current_thread = false;
47 if (signaling_thread) {
48 return signaling_thread;
49 }
50 auto this_thread = rtc::Thread::Current();
51 if (!this_thread) {
52 // If this thread isn't already wrapped by an rtc::Thread, create a
53 // wrapper and own it in this class.
54 this_thread = rtc::ThreadManager::Instance()->WrapCurrentThread();
55 wraps_current_thread = true;
56 }
57 return this_thread;
58}
59
60std::unique_ptr<SctpTransportFactoryInterface> MaybeCreateSctpFactory(
61 std::unique_ptr<SctpTransportFactoryInterface> factory,
62 rtc::Thread* network_thread) {
63 if (factory) {
64 return factory;
65 }
66#ifdef WEBRTC_HAVE_SCTP
67 return std::make_unique<cricket::SctpTransportFactory>(network_thread);
68#else
69 return nullptr;
70#endif
71}

75// Static
76rtc::scoped_refptr<ConnectionContext> ConnectionContext::Create(
77 PeerConnectionFactoryDependencies* dependencies) {
78 return new ConnectionContext(dependencies);
79}
80
81ConnectionContext::ConnectionContext(
82 PeerConnectionFactoryDependencies* dependencies)
83 : network_thread_(MaybeStartThread(dependencies->network_thread,
84 "pc_network_thread",
85 true,
86 owned_network_thread_)),
87 worker_thread_(MaybeStartThread(dependencies->worker_thread,
88 "pc_worker_thread",
89 false,
90 owned_worker_thread_)),
91 signaling_thread_(MaybeWrapThread(dependencies->signaling_thread,
92 wraps_current_thread_)),
93 network_monitor_factory_(
94 std::move(dependencies->network_monitor_factory)),
95 call_factory_(std::move(dependencies->call_factory)),
96 sctp_factory_(
97 MaybeCreateSctpFactory(std::move(dependencies->sctp_factory),
98 network_thread())),
99 trials_(dependencies->trials
100 ? std::move(dependencies->trials)
101 : std::make_unique<FieldTrialBasedConfig>()) {
102 signaling_thread_->AllowInvokesToThread(worker_thread_);
103 signaling_thread_->AllowInvokesToThread(network_thread_);
104 worker_thread_->AllowInvokesToThread(network_thread_);
105 if (network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
106 network_thread_->DisallowAllInvokes();
107 } else {
108 network_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask([thread = network_thread_] {
109 thread->DisallowBlockingCalls();
110 thread->DisallowAllInvokes();
111 }));
112 }
113
114 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
115 rtc::InitRandom(rtc::Time32());
116
117 // If network_monitor_factory_ is non-null, it will be used to create a
118 // network monitor while on the network thread.
119 default_network_manager_ = std::make_unique<rtc::BasicNetworkManager>(
120 network_monitor_factory_.get());
121
122 default_socket_factory_ =
123 std::make_unique<rtc::BasicPacketSocketFactory>(network_thread());
124
125 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&]() {
126 channel_manager_ = cricket::ChannelManager::Create(
127 std::move(dependencies->media_engine),
128 /*enable_rtx=*/true, worker_thread(), network_thread());
129 });
130
131 // Set warning levels on the threads, to give warnings when response
132 // may be slower than is expected of the thread.
133 // Since some of the threads may be the same, start with the least
134 // restrictive limits and end with the least permissive ones.
135 // This will give warnings for all cases.
136 signaling_thread_->SetDispatchWarningMs(100);
137 worker_thread_->SetDispatchWarningMs(30);
138 network_thread_->SetDispatchWarningMs(10);
139}
140
141ConnectionContext::~ConnectionContext() {
142 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread_);
143 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE,
144 [&]() { channel_manager_.reset(nullptr); });
145
146 // Make sure |worker_thread()| and |signaling_thread()| outlive
147 // |default_socket_factory_| and |default_network_manager_|.
148 default_socket_factory_ = nullptr;
149 default_network_manager_ = nullptr;
150
151 if (wraps_current_thread_)
152 rtc::ThreadManager::Instance()->UnwrapCurrentThread();
153}
154
155cricket::ChannelManager* ConnectionContext::channel_manager() const {
156 return channel_manager_.get();
157}
